{
  "version": 1,
  "description": "Eval questions for the contextual-retrieval pipeline. Each question's `expectedSubstrings` are unique-enough phrases that, if any one appears in a top-20 chunk's text, count the query as recalled. Multiple substrings = OR (any match counts). Curated 2026-04-26 from the repo's own docs (the corpus is the same set of files, so this measures recall against a fixed ground truth without needing human relevance judgments).",
